WEBVTT

00:20.200 --> 00:21.333
I'll be back!

00:21.400 --> 00:22.866
I'm free!

01:10.933 --> 01:12.100
Thanks for the ride.

01:12.166 --> 01:13.833
You're doing us the favor.

01:13.900 --> 01:16.466
Filling in
for our regular sitter.

01:16.533 --> 01:17.900
Here's the house.

01:18.933 --> 01:20.900
I know this place.

01:23.500 --> 01:25.300
You grew up here.

01:25.366 --> 01:27.700
Time to meet the kids.

01:27.766 --> 01:29.433
And I hope you like precocious.

01:38.600 --> 01:40.233
Is this her?

01:40.300 --> 01:41.633
Meet, Gina.

01:41.700 --> 01:45.033
When you watch them,
watch yourself.

01:45.100 --> 01:46.500
- Come on, Dan.
- Oh, my God, Cindy.

01:46.566 --> 01:49.366
- We can't just leave her here.
- Shut up!

01:49.433 --> 01:51.533
Do you wanna leave or not?

02:49.566 --> 02:51.333
It's just a phase!

02:51.400 --> 02:54.933
Roly-poly, fat and ugly.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.700
Roly-poly, fat and ugly.

03:12.200 --> 03:13.900
Ah!

03:19.800 --> 03:22.233
Hi, you must be Gina.

03:22.300 --> 03:24.866
I'm sorry it took so long,
I didn't hear the bell.

03:24.933 --> 03:27.366
Oh, don't worry,
I, uh, I just got that.

03:27.433 --> 03:29.033
Cindy Franklin.
How are ya?

03:29.100 --> 03:30.066
Good.

03:30.133 --> 03:31.300
Come on.

03:33.200 --> 03:35.866
'Here are my angels.'

03:35.933 --> 03:37.266
Say hi to Gina, she'll be
sitting with you tonight.

03:37.333 --> 03:39.333
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:40.266 --> 03:41.633
Ken, this is Gina.

03:41.700 --> 03:43.933
She's, uh, subbing
for Rita tonight.

03:44.000 --> 03:45.200
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:45.266 --> 03:47.500
Thanks for taking over
at such short notice.

03:47.566 --> 03:49.500
Rita tells us you're a model.

03:49.566 --> 03:50.933
Well, yeah, only part time.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.666
It just, it helps pay
my way through school.

03:53.733 --> 03:57.100
You certainly
have the figure for it.

03:57.166 --> 03:59.200
Well, I work on it.

04:00.933 --> 04:02.100
'Oh.'

04:06.833 --> 04:09.433
Few souvenirs from the academy.

04:09.500 --> 04:10.966
'My misspent youth
I'm afraid.'

04:11.033 --> 04:12.466
Uh, he ranked 10th in his class

04:12.533 --> 04:15.133
but gave up
his military career for me.

04:16.600 --> 04:18.900
So now I'm a lawyer.

04:18.966 --> 04:21.333
'Same attitude.
No khakis.'

04:22.666 --> 04:25.466
Now, I don't want you to worry.

04:25.533 --> 04:27.633
It's all securely locked u
and under control.

04:39.500 --> 04:41.300
Here's Ken's bosses number
in the mountains.

04:41.366 --> 04:44.000
It's about a three-hour drive
round trip.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.500
We should be back before 1:00.

04:45.566 --> 04:48.466
Oh, don't rush,
I have plenty of studying.

04:48.533 --> 04:51.066
And the fridge, it's packed with
food, in case you want a snack.

04:51.133 --> 04:53.333
Oh, thanks, but no thanks.

04:53.400 --> 04:55.633
I brought mine. Tsk.

04:55.700 --> 04:57.433
All you kids are on diets.

04:57.500 --> 04:59.833
Yeah, well, believe it or not,
I used to be a blimp.

04:59.900 --> 05:03.033
I mean, my answer to anxiety
was to eat..

05:03.100 --> 05:04.533
...everything else
within reach.

05:04.600 --> 05:07.233
Wow, you certainly cured
that habit.

05:07.300 --> 05:08.633
'Have a great time tonight.'

05:08.700 --> 05:09.900
'Okay, great,
I'm looking forward to it.'

05:09.966 --> 05:11.266
'Okay, goodnight.'

05:11.333 --> 05:12.466
- 'Goodnight.'
- 'Goodnight.'

05:12.533 --> 05:14.733
Okay, now
we're gonna have some fun.

05:14.800 --> 05:16.800
You guys wanna play
Monopoly or Twister

05:16.866 --> 05:19.366
Battleship, um, charades?

05:19.433 --> 05:22.133
- Whoa.
- Look, lamo.

05:22.200 --> 05:25.366
This is our house
and these are our rules.

05:25.433 --> 05:27.600
We eat what we want.
Watch what we want.

05:27.666 --> 05:29.400
'And go to bed when we want.'

05:29.466 --> 05:32.166
- Damn straight.
- You get the living room.

05:32.233 --> 05:34.433
And if you behave,
the kitchen

05:34.500 --> 05:36.066
when we're not in it.

05:36.133 --> 05:37.366
You don't hassle us..

05:37.433 --> 05:39.100
'...we don't hassle you.'

05:39.166 --> 05:41.133
Damn straight.

05:41.200 --> 05:43.833
Get it? Got it!
Good.

05:46.500 --> 05:48.933
Control,
I'm in control.

05:50.500 --> 05:51.800
'How's it going so far?'

05:51.866 --> 05:54.300
It is

05:54.366 --> 05:55.566
'Well, can't you make
friends with them?'

05:55.633 --> 05:56.766
No, they don't want
to be friends.

05:56.833 --> 05:58.666
'Have you tried?'

05:58.733 --> 06:01.133
Have I tried?
Yeah, kinda.

06:01.200 --> 06:03.100
So far they've tripped me,
trapped me

06:03.166 --> 06:05.466
booby-trapped
the staircase with slinkies.

06:05.533 --> 06:06.700
It's a horror show.

06:06.766 --> 06:08.733
- 'Sounds like a good time.'
- What can I do?

06:08.800 --> 06:10.600
'Well, you have to stay
in control.'

06:10.666 --> 06:11.866
- Yeah.
- 'You know that.'

06:11.933 --> 06:13.666
Well, you know what, Rita,
actually it's probably

06:13.733 --> 06:15.433
getting pretty late,
it's time to put

06:15.500 --> 06:16.800
the little darlings to bed.

06:16.866 --> 06:19.000
- 'Right, have fun.'
- Yeah, wish me luck.

06:19.066 --> 06:20.266
'Good luck,
see you in the morning.'

06:20.333 --> 06:22.633
- Okay. Thanks, bye.
- 'Bye.'

06:27.600 --> 06:29.666
Ricky, Dolly.

06:29.733 --> 06:32.500
It's time for bed.

06:35.700 --> 06:38.533
Ricky, Dolly.

06:40.533 --> 06:42.633
Where are you guys?

06:44.666 --> 06:46.066
It's story time,
where are you?

06:46.133 --> 06:48.633
Are you up in your room?

06:48.700 --> 06:50.700
Can you hear me?

06:51.633 --> 06:53.500
Ah!

06:53.566 --> 06:56.033
Come on,
where are you guys?

08:01.033 --> 08:02.433
Alright.

08:02.500 --> 08:04.633
Front and center right now.

08:12.200 --> 08:13.133
It was him.

08:13.200 --> 08:14.833
He pulled all the food
out of the fridge.

08:14.900 --> 08:17.033
It was her idea.
She told me to.

08:17.100 --> 08:18.733
- Did not.
- Did to.

08:18.800 --> 08:20.900
'It's not the mess
that I'm concerned with.'

08:20.966 --> 08:23.066
'Look at what you're eating,
look at this food.'

08:23.133 --> 08:24.433
It's junk food, it's poison.

08:24.500 --> 08:27.166
It's-it's high fat, low fiber.

08:27.233 --> 08:29.333
Heart attack food.

08:29.400 --> 08:33.333
- Roly-poly, fat and ugly.
- Roly-poly, fat and ugly.

08:35.733 --> 08:37.700
How could you know that?

08:40.300 --> 08:41.300
Oh.

08:41.366 --> 08:44.233
Okay, um,
off to bed with you guys.

08:44.300 --> 08:48.033
Just pick out a story and
I'll read it to you soon as I..

08:48.100 --> 08:50.333
...as soon as I
clean up this mess.

09:06.566 --> 09:08.633
Old habits die hard.

09:10.033 --> 09:14.033
Bet our babysitter
can't eat just one.

09:34.666 --> 09:36.566
Just come home.
Please come home.

09:36.633 --> 09:37.700
I gotta get out of here.

09:43.033 --> 09:44.166
- Hello.
- 'Hi, Gina.'

09:44.233 --> 09:46.500
'It's Cindy Franklin.
How are you doing?'

09:46.566 --> 09:47.866
'Enjoying yourself?'

09:47.933 --> 09:50.133
Oh, too much.

09:50.200 --> 09:53.200
'I'm glad to hear that
because we have a favor to ask.'

09:53.266 --> 09:55.233
'Would you mind
staying all night?'

09:57.166 --> 09:58.500
All night?

09:58.566 --> 10:01.000
I, um, I have a class, like,
really early in the morning.

10:01.066 --> 10:02.066
Tomorrow morning.

10:02.133 --> 10:04.400
'It's okay,
we'll be back before breakfast.'

10:04.466 --> 10:06.133
'Mr. Franklin had a bit
too much to drink'

10:06.200 --> 10:08.966
'and I can't see a thing
at night.'

10:09.033 --> 10:11.333
'Thanks, Gina,
we'll make it up to you.'

10:11.400 --> 10:13.333
'Keep up the good work.'

10:14.600 --> 10:18.200
Oh, God, control, control.

10:19.866 --> 10:22.033
I'm totally losing control.

10:55.233 --> 10:57.733
'Where's our story?'

10:59.300 --> 11:02.300
We might as well
read it ourselves.

11:03.600 --> 11:06.633
"Once upon a time,
there was a little boy.."

11:07.966 --> 11:09.066
I'm coming.

11:09.133 --> 11:11.633
Um, wait for a minute.

11:11.700 --> 11:13.733
If I can get through that door.

11:17.000 --> 11:19.600
I didn't forget about you.

11:19.666 --> 11:22.833
Alright, I'm gonna read you
a story in a minute.

11:22.900 --> 11:24.833
I'll be right there.

11:26.900 --> 11:28.033
No.

11:30.633 --> 11:32.933
- Right there.
- 'Wait.'

11:34.933 --> 11:37.033
'You can't be full yet.'

11:40.666 --> 11:42.600
What? You've had your fun,
and now we're history?

11:42.666 --> 11:44.300
Low fiber, high fat.

11:44.366 --> 11:46.233
No one's perfect,
bubblehead.

11:46.300 --> 11:48.766
Yeah, who're you calling
heart attack food?

11:48.833 --> 11:50.266
'Roly-poly.'

11:50.333 --> 11:51.833
It's just an expression.

11:51.900 --> 11:53.633
- All is forgiven.
- Yeah, sure.

11:53.700 --> 11:57.000
- Come on over and finish us.
- You know you want to.

12:38.066 --> 12:39.833
'Okay, guys,
sorry I dozed off.'

12:39.900 --> 12:42.233
But I can read you
a story now.

12:44.966 --> 12:48.000
Come out, come out
wherever you are.

12:51.700 --> 12:54.533
Come on, guys.

12:54.600 --> 12:56.300
We can, uh..

12:56.366 --> 12:58.800
...play pin the tail
on the sitter.

12:58.866 --> 13:00.933
You'll love that.

13:03.100 --> 13:05.600
Olly olly oxen free?

13:05.666 --> 13:07.300
God, remind me
never to have kids.

13:10.600 --> 13:12.533
How about a snack?

13:14.266 --> 13:15.300
'Okay.'

13:20.566 --> 13:21.633
Mm.

13:26.366 --> 13:27.400
Great.

13:28.533 --> 13:30.533
Cute, guys.

13:30.600 --> 13:32.700
Really cute.

13:32.766 --> 13:35.133
'What kind of a game
are we playing now?'

13:36.733 --> 13:40.300
Alright, you guys.

13:40.366 --> 13:41.633
You got me.

13:41.700 --> 13:43.633
Ha-ha.

13:47.733 --> 13:50.133
Where are you guys?

14:05.400 --> 14:07.333
Play time is over.

14:13.300 --> 14:14.966
Dolly!

14:15.033 --> 14:17.933
Dolly, where are you?

14:21.933 --> 14:23.000
Hello.

14:23.066 --> 14:24.000
'Gina?'

14:24.066 --> 14:25.700
Oh, Mrs. Franklin.

14:25.766 --> 14:27.533
'Yes, I'm sorry
to bother you again.'

14:27.600 --> 14:29.800
'I forgot to say goodnight
to the children.'

14:29.866 --> 14:32.700
- 'Can you put them on?'
- Well, uh..

14:32.766 --> 14:35.000
It's too late,
they're fast asleep.

14:35.066 --> 14:37.233
'Before midnight?'

14:37.300 --> 14:41.800
'I'm glad you and the children
have reached an understanding.'

14:47.600 --> 14:50.133
It's just a phase.

14:52.433 --> 14:53.833
'Just one thing.'

14:53.900 --> 14:55.000
Yeah?

14:55.066 --> 14:56.900
'When you watch them..'

14:56.966 --> 14:58.900
'...watch yourself.'

15:07.033 --> 15:09.000
Where are you guys?

15:10.233 --> 15:12.733
Why are you doing this to me?

15:14.333 --> 15:15.766
Oh, God.

15:15.833 --> 15:17.466
Where are you-you?

15:17.533 --> 15:18.633
No.

15:20.366 --> 15:22.166
What did I do to deserve this?

15:22.233 --> 15:24.300
There's no food.

15:25.033 --> 15:27.233
No, no. No!

15:27.300 --> 15:28.333
No!

15:28.400 --> 15:30.066
No, not when I'm really hungry.

15:30.133 --> 15:32.100
Oh, God.

15:32.166 --> 15:33.700
Control, control.

15:33.766 --> 15:35.366
Control.

15:35.433 --> 15:36.600
Okay.

15:41.766 --> 15:43.466
'Workers Anonymous hotline.'

15:43.533 --> 15:44.766
Oh, thank God.

15:44.833 --> 15:47.066
I am totally out of control.

15:47.133 --> 15:49.633
I don't want to eat anymore.

15:49.700 --> 15:51.566
I don't want to be fat.

15:51.633 --> 15:53.666
- Again.
- 'Just keep calm, ma'am.'

15:53.733 --> 15:55.166
'Now, what I really think you
should do is proceed'

15:55.233 --> 15:56.366
'to the freezer in the basement'

15:56.433 --> 15:58.266
'and roast the side of beef
and eat it up.'

15:58.333 --> 15:59.433
'It's just a phase.'

15:59.500 --> 16:02.200
'Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha.'

16:02.266 --> 16:03.400
Oh, God.

16:07.666 --> 16:08.833
Oh, God.

17:11.733 --> 17:14.066
You ate my big sister!

17:25.133 --> 17:26.500
No!

17:28.833 --> 17:30.833
Ricky.

17:31.866 --> 17:32.900
Ricky.

17:32.966 --> 17:35.500
Olly olly oxen free.

17:54.400 --> 17:55.400
'Ricky!'

17:57.900 --> 18:00.400
Ricky, come on, little buddy.

18:00.466 --> 18:03.366
Come on out,
I'm not gonna hurt ya.

18:03.433 --> 18:04.733
Just waste you a little.

18:07.866 --> 18:10.466
'Come on, Ricky.'

18:10.533 --> 18:13.933
'It's time for your story.'

18:19.566 --> 18:21.433
You
what I am..

18:21.500 --> 18:23.800
...so here I am.

18:26.066 --> 18:28.700
I smell finger food.

18:32.366 --> 18:34.200
You're not getting away.

18:42.200 --> 18:45.633
No one leaves until I'm full.

18:49.200 --> 18:52.100
Help! You have to send somebody.

18:52.166 --> 18:54.600
'Why bother? There's no way in.'

18:54.666 --> 18:55.733
Or out!

19:00.033 --> 19:02.700
It didn't have to be like this!

19:02.766 --> 19:04.733
Do you hear me?

19:05.666 --> 19:07.800
I was doing so well.

19:09.766 --> 19:11.133
You..

19:11.200 --> 19:13.533
And you played games with me.

19:14.533 --> 19:15.600
And you..

19:16.466 --> 19:18.900
You made me nervous!

19:18.966 --> 19:20.600
And..

19:20.666 --> 19:23.300
And you made me eat.

19:23.800 --> 19:24.800
And..

19:26.166 --> 19:28.233
You made me this.

19:30.700 --> 19:33.433
Roly-poly, fat and ugly!

19:33.500 --> 19:36.133
Roly-poly, fat and ugly!

19:36.200 --> 19:38.833
Roly-poly, fat and ugly!

19:38.900 --> 19:41.566
Roly-poly, fat and ugly!

19:41.633 --> 19:44.133
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:44.200 --> 19:46.533
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:46.600 --> 19:49.033
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:49.100 --> 19:51.466
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:51.533 --> 19:54.033
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:54.100 --> 19:56.566
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:56.633 --> 19:58.966
'Roly-poly, fat and ugly!'

19:59.033 --> 20:01.500
Roly-poly, fat and ugly!

21:22.133 --> 21:23.433
- 'Ricky?'
- 'Ricky!'

21:23.500 --> 21:24.933
'Ricky!'

21:25.000 --> 21:26.366
Here I am, mom.

21:26.433 --> 21:27.833
- Oh, thank God!
- Gina!

21:27.900 --> 21:29.233
Where's your sister?
Where is Gina?

21:29.300 --> 21:32.633
- Ricky.
- Gina! Gina!

21:32.700 --> 21:35.166
Gina, wake up.

21:35.233 --> 21:37.933
'Gina, wake up.'

21:38.000 --> 21:40.133
'Gina, wake up.'

21:40.200 --> 21:41.333
'Gina, wake up, honey.'

21:41.400 --> 21:43.066
- 'The sitter's here.'
- Mom!

21:43.133 --> 21:44.233
Gina, what's wrong?

21:44.300 --> 21:46.000
I was all grown up, mom.

21:46.066 --> 21:48.333
And I was sitting
for these two horrible kids.

21:48.400 --> 21:50.466
It's over, honey.
It was just a bad dream.

21:50.533 --> 21:52.700
I was&lt;

21:52.766 --> 21:54.433
Sweetie, you are beautiful.

21:54.500 --> 21:57.633
I was thin, mom.
Really thin.

21:57.700 --> 22:00.333
Oh, Gina, don't listen
to those kids at school

22:00.400 --> 22:01.866
when they tease you.

22:01.933 --> 22:04.100
This is just a phase.

22:07.666 --> 22:09.600
Here's the new sitter, baby.

22:10.900 --> 22:12.500
Hi, what's cookin'?

22:13.300 --> 22:15.233
Yummy.

22:17.100 --> 22:19.533
Maybe later you could
read Gina a story.

22:19.600 --> 22:20.933
- 'She likes that.'
- Oh, great!

22:21.000 --> 22:22.466
You know, I even brought one.

22:22.533 --> 22:24.500
Is, uh,
"Hansel And Gretel" okay?

22:39.833 --> 22:42.966
Little Gina
won't stay little for long.

22:43.033 --> 22:45.666
After all, you are who you eat.

23:08.400 --> 23:09.733
Gina..

23:11.400 --> 23:14.166
...you borrow my Walkman again?

23:14.233 --> 23:15.500
You want to do me a favor?

23:15.566 --> 23:18.466
Next time don't leave it
where daddy can step on it

23:18.533 --> 23:21.133
You can't just keep dropping
things wherever you like.

23:21.200 --> 23:23.133
Sorry, daddy.

23:23.200 --> 23:26.133
Someone got up
on the wrong side of bed.

23:26.200 --> 23:27.700
You know I've been working on
my brief for the last few weeks

23:27.766 --> 23:30.100
and I keep all my notes
on this thing.

23:30.166 --> 23:31.533
Ken!

23:36.800 --> 23:38.700
I understand
you're under pressure, babe

23:38.766 --> 23:42.000
butplease
try not to take it out on us.

23:42.066 --> 23:43.500
I'm just trying to work
on this case.

23:43.566 --> 23:45.300
It's very important.

23:45.366 --> 23:47.433
Might mean a partnership.
That's what you want, isn't it?

23:47.500 --> 23:50.633
You make it sound like
I forced you into law school.

23:50.700 --> 23:52.033
Well, let's just say

23:52.100 --> 23:54.966
it wasn't my first choice.

23:55.033 --> 23:57.500
Ah, look, Ken,
now is not the time

23:57.566 --> 23:59.133
to open that can of worms.

23:59.200 --> 24:01.433
I need you
to take Gina to school.

24:01.500 --> 24:03.133
What? You're kidding.

24:03.200 --> 24:05.000
I can't do that today,
I'm late already.

24:05.066 --> 24:06.600
One time
is not gonna kill you.

24:06.666 --> 24:08.233
I have a million things
to do today.

24:08.300 --> 24:09.333
Oh, and I don't?

24:09.400 --> 24:10.566
You know,
I'm really getting sick

24:10.633 --> 24:11.733
of being taken for granted

24:11.800 --> 24:13.266
Please, no whining.

24:13.333 --> 24:14.933
It is too early in the morning.

24:15.000 --> 24:17.066
Great, Cindy. You're right

24:17.133 --> 24:19.533
Men don't need any sympathy,
we should watch what we say..

24:19.600 --> 24:20.766
...and watch what we do..

24:20.833 --> 24:22.566
...spend our lives..

24:22.633 --> 24:24.833
...what, slaving
and breaking our backs.

24:24.900 --> 24:27.033
- Never complain.
- Ken, calm down.

24:27.100 --> 24:29.433
You should be happy
with what you have.

24:29.500 --> 24:30.866
Things could be much,
much worse.

24:30.933 --> 24:34.100
Yeah, well,
I feel like I'm in prison.

24:34.166 --> 24:36.166
What am I, 36 years old,
I have an earlier bedtime

24:36.233 --> 24:37.366
than when I was nine!

24:37.433 --> 24:39.000
My mother let me stay up
later than you do.

24:39.066 --> 24:40.633
Who are you kidding?

24:40.700 --> 24:43.433
You never want to go out.
You're always too tired.

24:43.500 --> 24:45.633
